3148
3149/*************************************************
3150* Execute a Regular Expression - DFA engine *
3151*************************************************/
3152
3153/* This external function applies a compiled re to a subject string using a DFA
3154engine. This function calls the internal function multiple times if the pattern
3155is not anchored.
3156
3157Arguments:
3158 argument_re points to the compiled expression
3159 extra_data points to extra data or is NULL
3160 subject points to the subject string
3161 length length of subject string (may contain binary zeros)
3162 start_offset where to start in the subject string
3163 options option bits
3164 offsets vector of match offsets
3165 offsetcount size of same
3166 workspace workspace vector
3167 wscount size of same
3168
3169Returns: > 0 => number of match offset pairs placed in offsets
3170 = 0 => offsets overflowed; longest matches are present
3171 -1 => failed to match
3172 < -1 => some kind of unexpected problem
3173*/
3174
3175#if defined COMPILE_PCRE8
3176PCRE_EXP_DEFN int PCRE_CALL_CONVENTION
3177pcre_dfa_exec(const pcre *argument_re, const pcre_extra *extra_data,
3178 const char *subject, int length, int start_offset, int options, int *offsets,
3179 int offsetcount, int *workspace, int wscount)
3180#elif defined COMPILE_PCRE16
3181PCRE_EXP_DEFN int PCRE_CALL_CONVENTION
3182pcre16_dfa_exec(const pcre16 *argument_re, const pcre16_extra *extra_data,
3183 PCRE_SPTR16 subject, int length, int start_offset, int options, int *offsets,
3184 int offsetcount, int *workspace, int wscount)
3185#elif defined COMPILE_PCRE32
3186PCRE_EXP_DEFN int PCRE_CALL_CONVENTION
3187pcre32_dfa_exec(const pcre32 *argument_re, const pcre32_extra *extra_data,
3188 PCRE_SPTR32 subject, int length, int start_offset, int options, int *offsets,
3189 int offsetcount, int *workspace, int wscount)
3190#endif
3191{
3192REAL_PCRE *re = (REAL_PCRE *)argument_re;
3193dfa_match_data match_block;
3194dfa_match_data *md = &match_block;
3195BOOL utf, anchored, startline, firstline;
3196const pcre_uchar *current_subject, *end_subject;
3197const pcre_study_data *study = NULL;
3198
3199const pcre_uchar *req_char_ptr;
3200const pcre_uint8 *start_bits = NULL;
3201BOOL has_first_char = FALSE;
3202BOOL has_req_char = FALSE;
3203pcre_uchar first_char = 0;
3204pcre_uchar first_char2 = 0;
3205pcre_uchar req_char = 0;
3206pcre_uchar req_char2 = 0;
3207int newline;
3208
3209/* Plausibility checks */
3210
3211if ((options & ~PUBLIC_DFA_EXEC_OPTIONS) != 0) return PCRE_ERROR_BADOPTION;
3212if (re == NULL || subject == NULL || workspace == NULL ||
3213 (offsets == NULL && offsetcount > 0)) return PCRE_ERROR_NULL;
3214if (offsetcount < 0) return PCRE_ERROR_BADCOUNT;
3215if (wscount < 20) return PCRE_ERROR_DFA_WSSIZE;
3216if (length < 0) return PCRE_ERROR_BADLENGTH;
3217if (start_offset < 0 || start_offset > length) return PCRE_ERROR_BADOFFSET;
3218
3219/* Check that the first field in the block is the magic number. If it is not,
3220return with PCRE_ERROR_BADMAGIC. However, if the magic number is equal to
3221REVERSED_MAGIC_NUMBER we return with PCRE_ERROR_BADENDIANNESS, which
3222means that the pattern is likely compiled with different endianness. */
3223
3224if (re->magic_number != MAGIC_NUMBER)
3225 return re->magic_number == REVERSED_MAGIC_NUMBER?
3226 PCRE_ERROR_BADENDIANNESS:PCRE_ERROR_BADMAGIC;
3227if ((re->flags & PCRE_MODE) == 0) return PCRE_ERROR_BADMODE;
3228
3229/* If restarting after a partial match, do some sanity checks on the contents
3230of the workspace. */
3231
3232if ((options & PCRE_DFA_RESTART) != 0)
3233 {
3234 if ((workspace[0] & (-2)) != 0 || workspace[1] < 1 ||
3235 workspace[1] > (wscount - 2)/INTS_PER_STATEBLOCK)
3236 return PCRE_ERROR_DFA_BADRESTART;
3237 }
3238
3239/* Set up study, callout, and table data */
3240
3241md->tables = re->tables;
3242md->callout_data = NULL;
3243
3244if (extra_data != NULL)
3245 {
3246 unsigned long int flags = extra_data->flags;
3247 if ((flags & PCRE_EXTRA_STUDY_DATA) != 0)
3248 study = (const pcre_study_data *)extra_data->study_data;
3249 if ((flags & PCRE_EXTRA_MATCH_LIMIT) != 0) return PCRE_ERROR_DFA_UMLIMIT;
3250 if ((flags & PCRE_EXTRA_MATCH_LIMIT_RECURSION) != 0)
3251 return PCRE_ERROR_DFA_UMLIMIT;
3252 if ((flags & PCRE_EXTRA_CALLOUT_DATA) != 0)
3253 md->callout_data = extra_data->callout_data;
3254 if ((flags & PCRE_EXTRA_TABLES) != 0)
3255 md->tables = extra_data->tables;
3256 }
3257
3258/* Set some local values */
3259
3260current_subject = (const pcre_uchar *)subject + start_offset;
3261end_subject = (const pcre_uchar *)subject + length;
3262req_char_ptr = current_subject - 1;
3263
3264#ifdef SUPPORT_UTF
3265/* PCRE_UTF(16|32) have the same value as PCRE_UTF8. */
3266utf = (re->options & PCRE_UTF8) != 0;
3267#else
3268utf = FALSE;
3269#endif
3270
3271anchored = (options & (PCRE_ANCHORED|PCRE_DFA_RESTART)) != 0 ||
3272 (re->options & PCRE_ANCHORED) != 0;
3273
3274/* The remaining fixed data for passing around. */
3275
3276md->start_code = (const pcre_uchar *)argument_re +
3277 re->name_table_offset + re->name_count * re->name_entry_size;
3278md->start_subject = (const pcre_uchar *)subject;
3279md->end_subject = end_subject;
3280md->start_offset = start_offset;
3281md->moptions = options;
3282md->poptions = re->options;
3283
3284/* If the BSR option is not set at match time, copy what was set
3285at compile time. */
3286
3287if ((md->moptions & (PCRE_BSR_ANYCRLF|PCRE_BSR_UNICODE)) == 0)
3288 {
3289 if ((re->options & (PCRE_BSR_ANYCRLF|PCRE_BSR_UNICODE)) != 0)
3290 md->moptions |= re->options & (PCRE_BSR_ANYCRLF|PCRE_BSR_UNICODE);
3291#ifdef BSR_ANYCRLF
3292 else md->moptions |= PCRE_BSR_ANYCRLF;
3293#endif
3294 }
3295
3296/* Handle different types of newline. The three bits give eight cases. If
3297nothing is set at run time, whatever was used at compile time applies. */
3298
3299switch ((((options & PCRE_NEWLINE_BITS) == 0)? re->options : (pcre_uint32)options) &
3300 PCRE_NEWLINE_BITS)
3301 {
3302 case 0: newline = NEWLINE; break; /* Compile-time default */
3303 case PCRE_NEWLINE_CR: newline = CHAR_CR; break;
3304 case PCRE_NEWLINE_LF: newline = CHAR_NL; break;
3305 case PCRE_NEWLINE_CR+
3306 PCRE_NEWLINE_LF: newline = (CHAR_CR << 8) | CHAR_NL; break;
3307 case PCRE_NEWLINE_ANY: newline = -1; break;
3308 case PCRE_NEWLINE_ANYCRLF: newline = -2; break;
3309 default: return PCRE_ERROR_BADNEWLINE;
3310 }
3311
3312if (newline == -2)
3313 {
3314 md->nltype = NLTYPE_ANYCRLF;
3315 }
3316else if (newline < 0)
3317 {
3318 md->nltype = NLTYPE_ANY;
3319 }
3320else
3321 {
3322 md->nltype = NLTYPE_FIXED;
3323 if (newline > 255)
3324 {
3325 md->nllen = 2;
3326 md->nl[0] = (newline >> 8) & 255;
3327 md->nl[1] = newline & 255;
3328 }
3329 else
3330 {
3331 md->nllen = 1;
3332 md->nl[0] = newline;
3333 }
3334 }
3335
3336/* Check a UTF-8 string if required. Unfortunately there's no way of passing
3337back the character offset. */
3338
3339#ifdef SUPPORT_UTF
3340if (utf && (options & PCRE_NO_UTF8_CHECK) == 0)
3341 {
3342 int erroroffset;
3343 int errorcode = PRIV(valid_utf)((pcre_uchar *)subject, length, &erroroffset);
3344 if (errorcode != 0)
3345 {
3346 if (offsetcount >= 2)
3347 {
3348 offsets[0] = erroroffset;
3349 offsets[1] = errorcode;
3350 }
3351#if defined COMPILE_PCRE8
3352 return (errorcode <= PCRE_UTF8_ERR5 && (options & PCRE_PARTIAL_HARD) != 0) ?
3353 PCRE_ERROR_SHORTUTF8 : PCRE_ERROR_BADUTF8;
3354#elif defined COMPILE_PCRE16
3355 return (errorcode <= PCRE_UTF16_ERR1 && (options & PCRE_PARTIAL_HARD) != 0) ?
3356 PCRE_ERROR_SHORTUTF16 : PCRE_ERROR_BADUTF16;
3357#elif defined COMPILE_PCRE32
3358 return PCRE_ERROR_BADUTF32;
3359#endif
3360 }
3361#if defined COMPILE_PCRE8 || defined COMPILE_PCRE16
3362 if (start_offset > 0 && start_offset < length &&
3363 NOT_FIRSTCHAR(((PCRE_PUCHAR)subject)[start_offset]))
3364 return PCRE_ERROR_BADUTF8_OFFSET;
3365#endif
3366 }
3367#endif
3368
3369/* If the exec call supplied NULL for tables, use the inbuilt ones. This
3370is a feature that makes it possible to save compiled regex and re-use them
3371in other programs later. */
3372
3373if (md->tables == NULL) md->tables = PRIV(default_tables);
3374
3375/* The "must be at the start of a line" flags are used in a loop when finding
3376where to start. */
3377
3378startline = (re->flags & PCRE_STARTLINE) != 0;
3379firstline = (re->options & PCRE_FIRSTLINE) != 0;
3380
3381/* Set up the first character to match, if available. The first_byte value is
3382never set for an anchored regular expression, but the anchoring may be forced
3383at run time, so we have to test for anchoring. The first char may be unset for
3384an unanchored pattern, of course. If there's no first char and the pattern was
3385studied, there may be a bitmap of possible first characters. */
3386
3387if (!anchored)
3388 {
3389 if ((re->flags & PCRE_FIRSTSET) != 0)
3390 {
3391 has_first_char = TRUE;
3392 first_char = first_char2 = (pcre_uchar)(re->first_char);
3393 if ((re->flags & PCRE_FCH_CASELESS) != 0)
3394 {
3395 first_char2 = TABLE_GET(first_char, md->tables + fcc_offset, first_char);
3396#if defined SUPPORT_UCP && !(defined COMPILE_PCRE8)
3397 if (utf && first_char > 127)
3398 first_char2 = UCD_OTHERCASE(first_char);
3399#endif
3400 }
3401 }
3402 else
3403 {
3404 if (!startline && study != NULL &&
3405 (study->flags & PCRE_STUDY_MAPPED) != 0)
3406 start_bits = study->start_bits;
3407 }
3408 }
3409
3410/* For anchored or unanchored matches, there may be a "last known required
3411character" set. */
3412
3413if ((re->flags & PCRE_REQCHSET) != 0)
3414 {
3415 has_req_char = TRUE;
3416 req_char = req_char2 = (pcre_uchar)(re->req_char);
3417 if ((re->flags & PCRE_RCH_CASELESS) != 0)
3418 {
3419 req_char2 = TABLE_GET(req_char, md->tables + fcc_offset, req_char);
3420#if defined SUPPORT_UCP && !(defined COMPILE_PCRE8)
3421 if (utf && req_char > 127)
3422 req_char2 = UCD_OTHERCASE(req_char);
3423#endif
3424 }
3425 }
3426
3427/* Call the main matching function, looping for a non-anchored regex after a
3428failed match. If not restarting, perform certain optimizations at the start of
3429a match. */
3430
3431for (;;)
3432 {
3433 int rc;
3434
3435 if ((options & PCRE_DFA_RESTART) == 0)
3436 {
3437 const pcre_uchar *save_end_subject = end_subject;
3438
3439 /* If firstline is TRUE, the start of the match is constrained to the first
3440 line of a multiline string. Implement this by temporarily adjusting
3441 end_subject so that we stop scanning at a newline. If the match fails at
3442 the newline, later code breaks this loop. */
3443
3444 if (firstline)
3445 {
3446 PCRE_PUCHAR t = current_subject;
3447#ifdef SUPPORT_UTF
3448 if (utf)
3449 {
3450 while (t < md->end_subject && !IS_NEWLINE(t))
3451 {
3452 t++;
3453 ACROSSCHAR(t < end_subject, *t, t++);
3454 }
3455 }
3456 else
3457#endif
3458 while (t < md->end_subject && !IS_NEWLINE(t)) t++;
3459 end_subject = t;
3460 }
3461
3462 /* There are some optimizations that avoid running the match if a known
3463 starting point is not found. However, there is an option that disables
3464 these, for testing and for ensuring that all callouts do actually occur.
3465 The option can be set in the regex by (*NO_START_OPT) or passed in
3466 match-time options. */
3467
3468 if (((options | re->options) & PCRE_NO_START_OPTIMIZE) == 0)
3469 {
3470 /* Advance to a known first pcre_uchar (i.e. data item) */
3471
3472 if (has_first_char)
3473 {
3474 if (first_char != first_char2)
3475 {
3476 pcre_uchar csc;
3477 while (current_subject < end_subject &&
3478 (csc = UCHAR21TEST(current_subject)) != first_char && csc != first_char2)
3479 current_subject++;
3480 }
3481 else
3482 while (current_subject < end_subject &&
3483 UCHAR21TEST(current_subject) != first_char)
3484 current_subject++;
3485 }
3486
3487 /* Or to just after a linebreak for a multiline match if possible */
3488
3489 else if (startline)
3490 {
3491 if (current_subject > md->start_subject + start_offset)
3492 {
3493#ifdef SUPPORT_UTF
3494 if (utf)
3495 {
3496 while (current_subject < end_subject &&
3497 !WAS_NEWLINE(current_subject))
3498 {
3499 current_subject++;
3500 ACROSSCHAR(current_subject < end_subject, *current_subject,
3501 current_subject++);
3502 }
3503 }
3504 else
3505#endif
3506 while (current_subject < end_subject && !WAS_NEWLINE(current_subject))
3507 current_subject++;
3508
3509 /* If we have just passed a CR and the newline option is ANY or
3510 ANYCRLF, and we are now at a LF, advance the match position by one
3511 more character. */
3512
3513 if (UCHAR21TEST(current_subject - 1) == CHAR_CR &&
3514 (md->nltype == NLTYPE_ANY || md->nltype == NLTYPE_ANYCRLF) &&
3515 current_subject < end_subject &&
3516 UCHAR21TEST(current_subject) == CHAR_NL)
3517 current_subject++;
3518 }
3519 }
3520
3521 /* Advance to a non-unique first pcre_uchar after study */
3522
3523 else if (start_bits != NULL)
3524 {
3525 while (current_subject < end_subject)
3526 {
3527 register pcre_uint32 c = UCHAR21TEST(current_subject);
3528#ifndef COMPILE_PCRE8
3529 if (c > 255) c = 255;
3530#endif
3531 if ((start_bits[c/8] & (1 << (c&7))) != 0) break;
3532 current_subject++;
3533 }
3534 }
3535 }
3536
3537 /* Restore fudged end_subject */
3538
3539 end_subject = save_end_subject;
3540
3541 /* The following two optimizations are disabled for partial matching or if
3542 disabling is explicitly requested (and of course, by the test above, this
3543 code is not obeyed when restarting after a partial match). */
3544
3545 if (((options | re->options) & PCRE_NO_START_OPTIMIZE) == 0 &&
3546 (options & (PCRE_PARTIAL_HARD|PCRE_PARTIAL_SOFT)) == 0)
3547 {
3548 /* If the pattern was studied, a minimum subject length may be set. This
3549 is a lower bound; no actual string of that length may actually match the
3550 pattern. Although the value is, strictly, in characters, we treat it as
3551 in pcre_uchar units to avoid spending too much time in this optimization.
3552 */
3553
3554 if (study != NULL && (study->flags & PCRE_STUDY_MINLEN) != 0 &&
3555 (pcre_uint32)(end_subject - current_subject) < study->minlength)
3556 return PCRE_ERROR_NOMATCH;
3557
3558 /* If req_char is set, we know that that pcre_uchar must appear in the
3559 subject for the match to succeed. If the first pcre_uchar is set,
3560 req_char must be later in the subject; otherwise the test starts at the
3561 match point. This optimization can save a huge amount of work in patterns
3562 with nested unlimited repeats that aren't going to match. Writing
3563 separate code for cased/caseless versions makes it go faster, as does
3564 using an autoincrement and backing off on a match.
3565
3566 HOWEVER: when the subject string is very, very long, searching to its end
3567 can take a long time, and give bad performance on quite ordinary
3568 patterns. This showed up when somebody was matching /^C/ on a 32-megabyte
3569 string... so we don't do this when the string is sufficiently long. */
3570
3571 if (has_req_char && end_subject - current_subject < REQ_BYTE_MAX)
3572 {
3573 register PCRE_PUCHAR p = current_subject + (has_first_char? 1:0);
3574
3575 /* We don't need to repeat the search if we haven't yet reached the
3576 place we found it at last time. */
3577
3578 if (p > req_char_ptr)
3579 {
3580 if (req_char != req_char2)
3581 {
3582 while (p < end_subject)
3583 {
3584 register pcre_uint32 pp = UCHAR21INCTEST(p);
3585 if (pp == req_char || pp == req_char2) { p--; break; }
3586 }
3587 }
3588 else
3589 {
3590 while (p < end_subject)
3591 {
3592 if (UCHAR21INCTEST(p) == req_char) { p--; break; }
3593 }
3594 }
3595
3596 /* If we can't find the required pcre_uchar, break the matching loop,
3597 which will cause a return or PCRE_ERROR_NOMATCH. */
3598
3599 if (p >= end_subject) break;
3600
3601 /* If we have found the required pcre_uchar, save the point where we
3602 found it, so that we don't search again next time round the loop if
3603 the start hasn't passed this point yet. */
3604
3605 req_char_ptr = p;
3606 }
3607 }
3608 }
3609 } /* End of optimizations that are done when not restarting */
3610
3611 /* OK, now we can do the business */
3612
3613 md->start_used_ptr = current_subject;
3614 md->recursive = NULL;
3615
3616 rc = internal_dfa_exec(
3617 md, /* fixed match data */
3618 md->start_code, /* this subexpression's code */
3619 current_subject, /* where we currently are */
3620 start_offset, /* start offset in subject */
3621 offsets, /* offset vector */
3622 offsetcount, /* size of same */
3623 workspace, /* workspace vector */
3624 wscount, /* size of same */
3625 0); /* function recurse level */
3626
3627 /* Anything other than "no match" means we are done, always; otherwise, carry
3628 on only if not anchored. */
3629
3630 if (rc != PCRE_ERROR_NOMATCH || anchored)
3631 {
3632 if (rc == PCRE_ERROR_PARTIAL && offsetcount >= 2)
3633 {
3634 offsets[0] = (int)(md->start_used_ptr - (PCRE_PUCHAR)subject);
3635 offsets[1] = (int)(end_subject - (PCRE_PUCHAR)subject);
3636 if (offsetcount > 2)
3637 offsets[2] = (int)(current_subject - (PCRE_PUCHAR)subject);
3638 }
3639 return rc;
3640 }
3641
3642 /* Advance to the next subject character unless we are at the end of a line
3643 and firstline is set. */
3644
3645 if (firstline && IS_NEWLINE(current_subject)) break;
3646 current_subject++;
3647#ifdef SUPPORT_UTF
3648 if (utf)
3649 {
3650 ACROSSCHAR(current_subject < end_subject, *current_subject,
3651 current_subject++);
3652 }
3653#endif
3654 if (current_subject > end_subject) break;
3655
3656 /* If we have just passed a CR and we are now at a LF, and the pattern does
3657 not contain any explicit matches for \r or \n, and the newline option is CRLF
3658 or ANY or ANYCRLF, advance the match position by one more character. */
3659
3660 if (UCHAR21TEST(current_subject - 1) == CHAR_CR &&
3661 current_subject < end_subject &&
3662 UCHAR21TEST(current_subject) == CHAR_NL &&
3663 (re->flags & PCRE_HASCRORLF) == 0 &&
3664 (md->nltype == NLTYPE_ANY ||
3665 md->nltype == NLTYPE_ANYCRLF ||
3666 md->nllen == 2))
3667 current_subject++;
3668
3669 } /* "Bumpalong" loop */
3670
3671return PCRE_ERROR_NOMATCH;
3672}
